CHANGES0028 - PropositionalTopology formalization (PropTopWork.agda)

New file: PropTopWork.agda (~510 lines, 0 holes, 0 postulates, COMPILES)

This file formalizes the propositional topology results from the tex file
(Open and closed propositions section). All results that dont need LLPO are proven.

Results proven:
1. Open⊓ - Conjunction of two open propositions is open (using ℕ×ℕ≅ℕ pairing)
2. Open⊓-prop - Truncated version
3. Open⊔ - Disjunction of two open propositions is open
4. negOpenWitnessIsClosedWitness / negOpenIsClosed - Negation of open is closed
5. negClosedWitnessIsOpenWitness / negClosedIsOpen - Negation of closed is open (needs wMP)
6. open-¬¬-stable - Open propositions are ¬¬-stable (needs wMP)
7. closed-¬¬-stable-witness - Closed propositions are ¬¬-stable (no axiom needed!)
8. decIsOpen / decIsClosed - Decidable propositions are open and closed
9. Closed⊓ - Conjunction of two closed propositions is closed (using ℕ⊎ℕ≅ℕ)
10. Closed⊓ω-witness - COUNTABLE conjunction of closed is closed (ℕ×ℕ≅ℕ)
11. Open⊔ω-witness - COUNTABLE disjunction of open is open (ℕ×ℕ≅ℕ)
12. impl-open-closed-witness - (P open, Q closed) implies (P→Q) is closed
13. impl-closed-open-witness - (P closed, Q open) implies (P→Q) is open (needs wMP)
14. ClosedMarkov-witness - For closed family Pn: ¬(∀n.Pn) → ∃n.¬Pn (needs wMP)

Key design decisions:
- Uses ¬' for type-level negation vs ¬ from Logic for hProp-level
- Countable operations use explicit witness families (no choice axiom needed)
- weakMarkovPrinciple stated locally, not imported from axioms module
- impl-open-closed uses γ(k) = α(fst(unpair k)) and β(snd(unpair k))
- impl-closed-open uses γ(k) = α(fst(unpair k)) or β(snd(unpair k))
- ClosedMarkov combines negClosedIsOpen + Markov on combined binary sequence

Not yet formalized (would need LLPO):
- Closed⊔ - Disjunction of two closed propositions is closed
- ClopenDecidable - If P is both open and closed, then P is decidable
